Nigerian Banks Agree $650 Million Loan for Etisalat, Punch Says

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-03-11T11:47:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/nigerian-banks-agree-650-million-loan-for-etisalat-punch-says.html
Etisalat  Nigeria  completed a $650
million loan deal with eight Nigerian banks to expand its mobile
phone network,  Punch  said, citing Chief Executive Officer Steven
Evans.  The loan is being arranged by First Bank of Nigeria Plc,
Zenith Bank Plc, Access Bank Plc, Fidelity Bank Plc and  United
Bank  for Africa Plc, the Lagos-based newspaper said. Others are
Bank PHB Plc, Guaranty Trust Bank Plc and Oceanic Bank
International Plc.  Etisalat Nigeria recently acquired Alheri Mobile Services
Ltd., a unit of the Dangote Group and a recipient of a 3G
license from the Nigerian Communications Commission, Punch said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 